reviewText: This is an expensive movie?! Is there anywhere I can buy mile post 398 at an offordable price?
it is a very very honest story about indian life on the rez.
I love it because I can relate to the life style. Being Native American and have lived on the Rez. I know how hard it to find a job there.

This is the real life today in the rez. Let's get out of the image of "Indians" living in tips and wearing deer skin clothes! I hope it'll open mentalities and contribute to help them for a better life. Our children's future in partly in their hands.
